### Wrexham Council

The entity known as [Wrexham County Borough Council](/Local_government_in_Wales) (or, for those who prefer the original tongue, *Cyngor Bwrdeistref Sirol Wrecsam*) serves as the principal governing authority for [Wrexham County Borough](/Wrexham_County_Borough). It’s a classic example of local government, attempting to exert some semblance of order over a [principal area](/Principal_area_of_Wales) in [north](/North_Wales) [Wales](/Wales)—an area that, with a certain bureaucratic flourish, even secured [city status](/City_status_in_the_United_Kingdom) in 2022. Essentially, it’s the administrative apparatus overseeing the urban sprawl of [Wrexham](/Wrexham) and its surrounding, often less-heralded, environs.

