In the grand scheme of local governance, the role of [Mayor of Wrexham](/Mayor_of_Wrexham) is, to put it mildly, largely ceremonial. It's a position steeped in tradition and civic representation, involving ribbon-cutting and pleasantries, but wielding little in the way of direct political power. The actual, gritty business of political leadership falls squarely upon the shoulders of the [leader of the council](/Leader_of_the_council). This individual navigates the choppy waters of council meetings, coalition demands, and public expectations.

